OL,4,Cover 'phenomenal' development plans
OL,6,FThe County Hall building was
OL,7,Foriginally built in the Victorian
OL,8,Ftimes. Back when it opened in 1853, it
OL,9,Fwas called Smedley's Hydro and for
OL,10,Fmany years was home to a spa offering
OL,11,Fa variety of different baths and water
OL,12,Ftreatments.
OL,14,FSmedley's Hydro helped transform
OL,15,FMatlock's image from a little known
OL,16,Fvillage to a wealthy town.
OL,18,FThe spa went into decline after the
OL,19,FGreat War and eventually became
OL,20,FDerbyshire County Hall in the 1950s.
